THE PILOT WAS INFORMED DURING WX BRIEFING THAT VFR WAS NOT 
RECOMMENDED BECAUSE OF LOW CLOUDS. PILOT ELECTED TO TAKEOFF AND FOLLOW 
I-90, HOWEVER, WX CONDITIONS WERE POOR AND PILOT EXECUTED A CLIMB TO 
10000 FEET TO CLEAR THE CLOUD LAYER. WHILE EN ROUTE THE PILOT TUNED TO THE 
ASHVILLE VOR AND TRACKED TO A LOCATION HE THOUGHT WAS IN THE VICINITY 
OF THE ARPT. A DESCENT WAS MADE THROUGH BREAKS IN THE CLOUDS TO 5500 FT. 
THE DESCENT WAS THEN CONTINUED TO 4000 FEET WHERE THE PILOT APPLIED POWER 
AND THE AIRCRAFT CONTACTED A MOUNTAIN. 
